<!--Title: Topic View Helpers-->

<markdown>

<Section title="Link to a Topic in the same Project" id="topics">
To link to a topic within the same project, just use:

<Snippet name="using-topic-link" />
which renders:

<!-- SAMPLE: using-topic-link -->
<TopicLink name="codesnippets" />
<!-- ENDSAMPLE -->
</Section>

<Section title="Link to a Topic in a different Project" id="external-link">

To link to a topic in a different project, use:

<Snippet name="using-external-link" />

which renders:

<!-- SAMPLE: using-external-link -->
<ExternalTopicLink title="More about Code Snippets" name="fubudocs/codesnippets" />
<!-- ENDSAMPLE -->

Note that in the usage of <code>&lt;ExternalTopicLink&gt;</code> you'll need to specify the project name as part of the name attribute.  

</Section>


<Section title="Link to another Project" id="projects">

<Snippet name="ProjectLink" />
  

<!-- SAMPLE: ProjectLink -->
<ProjectLink name="FubuMVC.CodeSnippets" />
<!-- ENDSAMPLE -->

</Section>

<Section title="Table of Contents" id="toc">

You can add a table of contents for all the topics beneath the current topic by using the <code>&lt;TableOfContents /&gt;</code> binding.

</Section>

<Section title="Project Summary" id="summary">
You can display the project summary for the current project with the <code>&lt;ProjectSummary /&gt;</code> binding.
</Section>

<Section title="Information Balloons" id="balloons">
As a convenience method, use the <code>&lt;Info&gt;[text]&lt;/Info&gt;</code> binding as a shortcut for Twitter Bootstrap balloons like this:

<Info>I'm an informational bullet!</Info>
</Section>


  <Section title="Nugets" id="nugets">
Use this helper:

<Snippet name="nuget-helper" />

which renders:   
    
<!-- SAMPLE: nuget-helper-->
<Nuget name="FubuMVC.Core" />
<!-- ENDSAMPLE -->    
  </Section>

  <Section title="Gems" id="gems">
Use this helper:

<Snippet name="gem-helper" />

which renders:

<!-- SAMPLE: gem-helper-->
<Gem name="ripple-cli" />
<!-- ENDSAMPLE -->
  </Section>
  
</markdown>


